Seems to have to do with namespacing:
```using ModelingToolkit
using OrdinaryDiffEq

function springmass()
  @parameters t
  @variables x(t)
  D = Differential(t)
  @parameters M b k
  eqs = [D(D(x)) ~ 1/M * (-b*D(x) - k*x )] # equations defining the system
  iv = t # the independent variable
  states = [x] # the dependent (state) variables
  ps = [M, b, k] # parameter variables
  default_u0 = [D(x) =&gt; 0.0, x =&gt; 1.5] # default initial conditions
  default_p = [M =&gt; 1.0, b =&gt; 1.0, k =&gt; 1.0] # default parameter values
  @named smd_sys = ODESystem(eqs, iv, states, ps, default_u0=default_u0, default_p=default_p)
  return ode_order_lowering(smd_sys)
end
smd_sys = springmass()
u0 = [smd_sys.x =&gt; -1.0] # initial conditions (empty = use defaults)
prob = ODEProblem(smd_sys, u0, (0.0, 1.0))
@show prob.u0 # prob.u0 = [0.0, 1.5] # hasn't been updated
sol = solve(prob, Tsit5())
@show sol.u[1] # sol.u[1] = [0.0, 1.5] # same```
If I do the same but without the function and just `u0 = [x =&gt; -1.0]` it works as expected.

